h1 How to install into Anki

p In WaniKani to Anki exporter choose any of the exporter options and save the file locally.

p Note: The comments at the top of the file define the field header names and these are currently <em>#key;type;character;meaning;image;onyomi;kunyomi;important_reading;kana;level</em> which are the merged fields returned by <a href="https://www.wanikani.com/api">https://www.wanikani.com/api</a>

h2 Create the WaniKani Note Type
p Start Anki and choose <em>Tools > Manage Note Types</em>. 

p Click the <em>Add</em> button, select <em>"Add: Basic"</em> and click <em>Ok</em>. Type in <em>WaniKani</em> for the <em>Note Type Name</em> and click <em>Ok</em>

p For each of the field headers above, click <em>Add</em> to create a new field in Anki.

img src="images/anki_fields_for_WaniKani.png"

h2 Create the Deck Definition

p <em>Tools > Study Deck...</em>

p click <em>Add</em> and in the New deck name enter <em>WaniKani</em>, and click <em>Ok</em>.

p Cancel the Study Deck dialog

h2 Create the Card Definition

p On the main page of Anki click the <em>Add</em> button at the top

p In the dialog make sure the <em>Type</em> is "WaniKani" and <em>Deck</em> is "WaniKani"

p Click the <em>Cards...</em> button

h3 WaniKani cards

p At the bottom of the <em>Card Types for WaniKani</em> window click the <em>More</em> button and click <em>Rename</em>, type <em>WaniKani</em> and click <em>Ok</em>

p For <em>Front Template</em> use

p
  pre
    code 
      / Use http://www.freeformatter.com/html-escape.html to escape the Anki 
      ' 
        &lt;div class=&quot;ja {{type}}&quot;&gt;
        {{#character}}{{character}}{{/character}}
        {{#image}}{{image}}{{/image}}
        &lt;/div&gt;

